Here it is folks!

That should give you a great start to kerning your typefaces! One other trick I use is when I want to try my fonts in context I go to a big news site like nytimes.com and change the body typeface in the CSS of the page in the developper menu. More info on this here. Its really easy to spot any aberrations that way. If you want to go into more details with you kerning you can use the content here. Theres less context but you pretty much have all the possible pairs there.

Thank you so much for reading!",
